T*
T*
(5\) DAG execution flow in detail) Tj
T*
(DAG ID: ai_quant_daily_pipeline.) Tj
T*
(Asset classes covered:) Tj
T*
(- crypto) Tj
T*
(- nifty50) Tj
T*
(- nifty_midcap) Tj
T*
(- nifty_smallcap) Tj
T*
(- mutual_funds) Tj
T*
T*
(Per asset class, the logical chain is:) Tj
T*
(ingest -> spark_etl -> train_model -> generate_signals -> audit_etl -> quality_check -> reconcile) Tj
T*
T*
(Scheduling behavior:) Tj
T*
(- crypto and nifty50 run in parallel first.) Tj
T*
(- midcap, smallcap, and mutual funds then run sequentially to reduce memory pressure.) Tj
T*
(- after all branches: generate_daily_audit_report -> send_opportunity_email) Tj
T*
T*
(6\) Ingestion layer internals) Tj
T*
(6.1 Binance ingestion \(src/ingestion/binance_ingest.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Pulls klines from Binance public API using symbols from settings.BINANCE.) Tj
T*
(- Writes to bronze.crypto_price_raw.) Tj
T*
(- Uses UNIQUE\(symbol, event_time\) and ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING for idempotency.) Tj
T*
T*
(6.2 NSE + Yahoo Finance ingestion \(src/ingestion/yfinance_ingest.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Dynamically fetches index constituents from NSE CSV endpoints.) Tj
T*
(- Uses yfinance per symbol and captures longName as asset_name when possible.) Tj
T*
(- Implements incremental loading by pre-reading MAX\(event_time\) per symbol.) Tj
T*
(- Writes to bronze.<index>_price_raw with asset_name field.) Tj
T*
T*
(6.3 Mutual fund ingestion \(src/ingestion/mfapi_ingest.py\)) Tj
T*
(- Discovers schemes from MFAPI, filtered by top AMC keywords + Direct Growth constraint.) Tj
T*
(- Fetches NAV history concurrently with ThreadPoolExecutor.) Tj
T*
(- Applies incremental date filtering and inserts/upserts into bronze.mutual_funds_price_raw.) Tj
T*
T*
(7\) Spark ETL internals \(src/etl/pyspark_etl.py\)) Tj
T*
(Main function: run_spark_etl\(source_table, dest_table\).) Tj
T*
T*
(Execution steps:) Tj
T*
(- Create SparkSession tuned for Docker memory constraints and adaptive execution.) Tj
T*
(- Determine source MIN\(id\), MAX\(id\), COUNT\(*\) in Postgres.) Tj
T*
(- Choose JDBC partition strategy:) Tj
T*
(  - if min/max present, parallel JDBC read using id bounds.) Tj
T*
(  - else fallback to single partition read.) Tj
T*
(- Cast numeric columns and repartition by symbol before window functions.) Tj
T*
(- Compute indicators with Spark windows in compute_indicators:) Tj
ET
endstream
