(Threshold mapping examples:) Tj
T*
(- 1y >= 0.72 -> INVEST NOW) Tj
T*
(- 1y >= 0.58 -> ACCUMULATE) Tj
T*
(- 5y >= 0.70 -> STRONG HOLD) Tj
T*
T*
(Gold table schema:) Tj
T*
(- symbol, trade_date) Tj
T*
(- signal, confidence \(primary 1-year view\)) Tj
T*
(- signal_1y, confidence_1y) Tj
T*
(- signal_5y, confidence_5y) Tj
T*
T*
(Upsert behavior:) Tj
T*
(- PRIMARY KEY \(symbol, trade_date\)) Tj
T*
(- ON CONFLICT updates signal and confidence columns.) Tj
T*
T*
(10\) Report and email pipeline \(src/recommendation/email_alert.py\)) Tj
T*
(Main function: send_opportunity_email\(\).) Tj
T*
T*
(Report generation behavior:) Tj
T*
(- Reads latest signals + latest features per symbol for each asset class.) Tj
T*
(- Includes asset_name \(fallback to symbol if asset_name missing\).) Tj
T*
(- Filters rows where any signal column is one of:) Tj
T*
(  INVEST NOW, ACCUMULATE, STRONG BUY, BUY) Tj
T*
(- Writes one worksheet per asset class into an XLSX file.) Tj
T*
T*
(Formatting behavior:) Tj
T*
(- Green row highlight if any signal column is INVEST NOW.) Tj
T*
(- confidence columns displayed as percentages using 0.00% number format.) Tj
T*
T*
(SMTP behavior:) Tj
T*
(- Reads credentials from environment, then Airflow Variables as fallback.) Tj
T*
(- Supports multiple recipients \(comma or semicolon separated\).) Tj
T*
(- If default XLSX path is locked, writes to timestamped fallback filename.) Tj
T*
T*
